Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Rio Alto Mining, Volcan Decline

-- B y   J o h n   Q u i g l e y
-- 
2011-10-13T17:01:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-13/peru-stocks-buenaventura-rio-alto-mining-volcan-decline.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Peru trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 11:28 a.m. Lima time.  The Lima General Index fell 0.6 percent to 18,449.87. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index retreated 1 percent to 2,427.58.  Copper and zinc producers fell as the metals declined in
 New York  on concern that  Europe ’s sovereign-debt crisis will
damp global growth and curb Chinese demand.  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE), the country’s largest
zinc producer, fell 1.6 percent to 2.51 soles.  Gold companies declined as gains in the dollar curbed
demand for the metal as an alternative asset.  Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s
biggest precious-metals miner, fell the most in a week, easing
1.2 percent to $41.50.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian
gold exploration company, dropped 4.1 percent to $2.57.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Quigley in Lima at 
 jquigley8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos at 
 papadopoulos@bloomberg.net  